SIMPLE: sofa
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sofa
<hw>So"fa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Sofas</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Ar. <ets>soffah</ets>, from
<ets>saffa</ets> to dispose in order: cf. F. <ets>sofa</ets>, It.
<ets>sof⟦agrave⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>A long seat, usually with a
cushioned bottom, back, and ends; -- much used as a comfortable piece of
furniture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let fall the curtains, wheel the <qex>sofa</qex> round.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sofa bed</b></col>, <cd>a sofa so contrived that it may
be extended to form a bed; -- called also <altname>sofa
bedstead</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soffit</ent>⟦br⟧
